text.paragraph:
Patients with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (e.g., chronic bronchitis, emphysema) of mild or moderate severity, bronchospastic disease, or a history of bronchospastic disease (other than bronchial asthma or a history of bronchial asthma, in which brimonidine tartrate/timolol maleate ophthalmic solution is contraindicated 
                              [see Contraindications (4.1)]
                           ) should, in general, not receive beta-blocking agents, including brimonidine tartrate/timolol maleate ophthalmic solution.
